    "As can be seen from Table 6, the models exhibit notably better performance under random conditions compared to out-of-sample conditions.",
    "Specifically, the BH dataset shows exceptionally high R 2 values exceeding 0.95, which is remarkably high in practical scenarios.",
    "This suggests that the model performance may be overestimated when using random splits, potentially leading to misleading conclusions.",
